2. 

In these Regulations- 

“Act” means Animal Health and Welfare Act 2013; 

“ear-cropping” means the removal of all or part of the ear of a dog – 

(a) 

for a purpose other than the diagnosis or treatment of injury, 
disease or infection, or 

(b) by a person other than a veterinary practitioner; 

“licence” means a licence under Regulation 5. 

